    "doc": "TWIHS EEPROM emulation",
    "title": "Running the Application",
    "content": ". | Open the twihs_eeprom application from apps/twihs/master/twihs_eeprom/firmware and open the main.c file. Make sure the following macro is defined to false. #define I2C_SLAVE_IS_ONBOARD_EEPROM false . | Build and program TWIHS EEPROM application from apps/twihs/master/twihs_eeprom/firmware onto the evaluation kit used as TWIHS master | Build and Program TWIHS slave application onto the evaluation kit used as TWIHS slave | Run application on TWIHS slave board and then run the application on TWIHS master board | LED on the TWIHS master board indicates success or failure: . | The LED is turned ON when the value read from the TWIHS slave matches with the written value | The LED is turned OFF when the value read from the TWIHS slave did not match with the written value | . | . ",
